For instance instead of the circle a simple dot that lights up green on input and red on deletion?</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Dec 2014 13:04:52 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5152/customize-the-i3lock-unlock-indicator/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Adaephon for &lt;p&gt;Is there a way to customize the i3lock's unlock-indicator?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For instance instead of the circle a simple dot that lights up green on input and red on deletion?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5152/customize-the-i3lock-unlock-indicator/?answer=5153#post-id-5153</link><description>You can disable the indicator with

    i3lock -u

Any other indicator customizations are not possible at the moment.</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Dec 2014 13:25:28 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5152/customize-the-i3lock-unlock-indicator/?answer=5153#post-id-5153</guid></item><item><title>Comment by daedalus.mythos for &lt;p&gt;You can disable the indicator with&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;i3lock -u
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any other indicator customizations are not possible at the moment.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5152/customize-the-i3lock-unlock-indicator/?comment=5154#comment-5154</link><description>thank you for the answer. I'm currently using the -u flag with the -p win :)</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Dec 2014 13:37:09 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5152/customize-the-i3lock-unlock-indicator/?comment=5154#comment-5154</guid></item></channel></rss>